{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Chicken","content":["With a sharp knife, make several deep slashes in the chicken pieces, cutting down to the bone. Place in a large plastic food bag.","Place oil, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard powder, coriander, cumin, ginger and salt in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer sauce to plastic bag with chicken and toss until well coated. Seal bag and set aside in fridge for at least 1 hour (see tip). Clean mixing bowl.","Once chicken has marinated, preheat oven to 190°C. Arrange chicken pieces in a non-stick roasting tin and pour marinade over. Roast for 35-40 minutes (190°C) until dark brown and cooked. Meanwhile, make coleslaw."]},{"title":"Coleslaw","content":["Place onion, carrots, cabbage, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>4 sec\/speed 4.5<\/nobr>, while stirring with spatula through hole in mixing bowl lid. Serve with hot, cooked chicken."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Chicken","content":["1000 g chicken, thighs and drumsticks, skin on","30 g olive oil","100 g tomato ketchup","1 Tbsp Worcestershire sauce","2 tsp English mustard powder","1 tsp ground coriander","1 tsp ground cumin","¼ tsp ground ginger","1 pinch fine sea salt"]},{"title":"Coleslaw","content":["25 g onion","50 g carrots, cut in pieces","300 g cabbage, red or green or a mixture of both, cut in pieces","50 g mayonnaise","1 tsp lemon juice","¼ - ½ tsp fine sea salt, to taste","2 pinches ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r95605","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-d39sZSrgKy8\/XZQui2UzqWI\/AAAAAAAAcUc\/opdphtt97HkCoApOIM6GVEm2RoofrwvPwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_24DFHCQIuc-mawfb.png","title":"Devilled Chicken with Coleslaw","publishedAt":"2016-06-27T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"38.2 g","fat":"34.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"9.5 g","calories":"2095 kJ \/ 501 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large food bag, long sharp knife, roasting tin, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Serve with a jacket potato or green salad.","The longer the chicken is left to marinate, the better the end flavour."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","45m","6 portions"]}